<?xml version="1.0"?>
<!--
    <tag name="foo">
       <tag name="bar" root="true">
       <tag name="baz">
       ...
    <tag name="bar:" pseudo="true">
       <tag name="boo"  parents="bar baz">
       ...

    Attribute root="true|false"
        The tag is a root tag which is somehow significant in the hierarchy.
        This will be reflected in the UI - for instance, these will be offered to the user for filtering and grouping.
        For example: "java-ee" is a root tag, while some minor technologies and APIs are not.

    Attribute pseudo:
        The tag is not supposed to appear in the UI, but can still serve as grouping for other tags and for referencing it by the parents="..." atribute.

    Attribute parents:
        A coma or white-space separated list of tag names.
        The tag belongs, besides it's XML structure parent tag, also under the referenced parent tags.

    Attribute color:
        Suggestion for the UI on which color to use for a label.

    Attribute url:
        An URL to a relevant documentation or definition. For example, the license homepage for license-* tags.
-->
